# 5. CODING STANDARDS
- Naming: snake_case for variables/functions, PascalCase for classes.
- Documentation: Include concise docstrings for all core logic so the user doesn't have to guess what a function does a month from now.
- Error Handling: Fail gracefully. Use Try/Except blocks extensively, especially around file I/O and network calls.

# 6. TOOL MASTERY & TOKEN EFFICIENCY
